tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE genome_sequences (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sequence TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE genes (
  gene_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_name TEXT,
  chromosome INT,
  start_position INT,
  end_position INT
)

CREATE TABLE mutations (
  mutation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_id INT,
  mutation_type TEXT,
  mutation_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE analysis_results (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_id INT,
  mutation_id INT,
  analysis_date DATE,
  analysis_result TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE PatientData (
  patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  patient_name VARCHAR(50),
  genetic_sequence TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE GeneticVariants (
  variant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  variant_name VARCHAR(50),
  variant_type VARCHAR(20),
  gene_id INT,
  chromosome_number INT
)

CREATE TABLE GeneInfo (
  gene_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gene_name VARCHAR(50),
  gene_function TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE TestResults (
  test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  patient_id INT,
  variant_id INT,
  test_date DATE,
  result VARCHAR(10)
)

CREATE TABLE LabTechnicians (
  technician_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  technician_name VARCHAR(50),
  lab_department VARCHAR(50)
)
